# Copy this file to `.env.local` (git-ignored) and fill in real values from
# your Supabase project's Project Settings → API page. See
# server/supabase/docs/backend.md for the full provisioning checklist.
#
# Leaving BOTH of these unset (the default for a plain checkout / CI) makes
# the app run entirely against the Local/demo backend (localStorage) — no
# error, no network calls. Setting only one of the two also falls back to
# Local (see apps/web/src/adapters/factory.ts).
#
# The anon key is safe to expose in client code — Row Level Security (see
# server/supabase/migrations/0001_init.sql) is the actual access boundary.
# NEVER put the service_role key here or anywhere in this repo.

VITE_SUPABASE_URL=
VITE_SUPABASE_ANON_KEY=

# Google OAuth **client ID** (NOT the secret) from Google Cloud Console →
# API 및 서비스 → 사용자 인증 정보. Enables the on-origin GIS sign-in button
# (Google's consent screen then shows OUR domain instead of the supabase.co
# callback). Unset → the login page falls back to the redirect OAuth flow.
# Client IDs are public by design (they ship in every browser bundle); the
# client SECRET stays in the Supabase dashboard only, never in this repo.
VITE_GOOGLE_CLIENT_ID=
